In his remarks to the Congress of the United States, President Trump laid out his agenda for the coming year. He emphasized the need for unity and cooperation, stating that the agenda he presented is not partisan but represents the interests of the American people. He highlighted the achievements of his administration so far, including job creation, economic growth, tax cuts, and criminal justice reform. He also addressed issues such as immigration, healthcare, trade, national security, and foreign policy. The President called for bipartisan action on issues such as infrastructure, reducing drug prices, and protecting patients with pre-existing conditions. He also urged Congress to pass legislation to secure the southern border and to prohibit late-term abortions. The President emphasized the importance of defending American interests and the need for a strong military, while also pursuing peace and diplomacy. He concluded his remarks by urging Americans to choose greatness and to work together to achieve a bright future for the nation.